description: Calcutta High Court acquitted a man who served seven years for his brother’s murder due to lack of conclusive evidence. The court found serious discrepancies in the investigation and noted failures such as the absence of forensic tests and unreliability of circumstantial evidence presented by the prosecution.
title: After 7 years in jail, Kolkata man acquitted of brother's murder

description: Congress is contesting just 11 seats in Mumbai assembly polls, the lowest in decades. Despite multiple negotiations with Shiv Sena (UBT), the party secured these seats, some being BJP strongholds. Mumbai Congress President Varsha Gaikwad admits they aimed for 14-15 seats but will work towards maximizing MVA wins despite the limited allocation.
title: Congress contesting only 11 of 36 Mumbai seats, down from 30 in 2019

description: Shiv Sena candidate Shaina NC filed an FIR against Shiv Sena (UBT) MP Arvind Sawant for alleged objectionable remarks he made against her. The case was registered under sections 79 and 356 (2) of the BNS. Sawant denied using any insulting words and questioned the timing and other allegations against Sena leaders.
title: Shaina NC lodges FIR against UBT MP Arvind Sawant for 'offensive' remark

description: India and the US commenced their 15th 'Vajra Prahar' exercise at the Orchard Combat Training Centre in Idaho. The drill, involving Para-SF units from India and Green Berets from the US, aims to enhance interoperability and joint special operations capabilities. It includes joint planning, UAV usage, and psychological warfare, among others.
title: India, US armies to begin 'Vajra Prahar' drill in Idaho today

description: Prime Minister Modi on Friday accused the Congress of making unrealistic promises and highlighted the challenges of implementing them. Modi urged vigilance against the Congress's 'culture of fake promises,' emphasizing that they often pledge things they can't deliver. Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge acknowledged the need to consider fiscal constraints.
title: Congress badly exposed due to unreal promises, be vigilant against party's culture of fake pledges: PM Modi

description: A toxin produced by fungus-infected kodo grain is suspected in the deaths of 10 elephants at Bandhavgarh Tiger Reserve. Autopsies revealed severe organ damage, suggesting toxic grain ingestion. Officials are monitoring the remaining elephants, destroying affected crops, and investigating other potential causes, including foul play.
title: Toxic grains may have killed Madhya Pradesh's 10 elephants

description: The Vishwa Hindu Parishad welcomed Donald Trump's condemnation of violence against Hindus and other minorities in Bangladesh, contrasting it with the silence of the United Nations and human rights activists. VHP functionary Vinod Bansal praised Trump for acknowledging the seriousness of the situation and criticized the lack of global response.
title: 'Welcome step': VHP hails Trump for standing by Hindus in Bangladesh

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi emphasized national unity, asserting that unity ensures safety. Speaking on National Unity Day, he warned against forces like 'urban Naxals' and external entities aiming to destabilize India. Modi highlighted initiatives like 'one nation, one tax' and the proposed 'one nation, one election', drawing on Sardar Patel's legacy of unification.
title: Ek rahenge to safe rahenge: PM's 'unity' mantra on Patel birth anniversary

description: NSA Ajit Doval and US counterpart Jake Sullivan discussed enhancing bilateral ties, including defence and security cooperation, and addressing regional and global stability. They also highlighted future collaborations in clean energy and defence. The discussions occurred amid tensions over murder-for-hire allegations involving India's Home Minister Amit Shah.
title: Doval holds talks with US NSA on defence, Indo-Pacific

description: Retail car sales in India surged by 26% in October, driven by festivals such as Navratri, Dussehra, Dhanteras, and Diwali. Maruti recorded its highest-ever October sales with over 2 lakh units, and demand was notably strong in rural areas.
title: Auto retail sales rise 26% on festive push

description: Goa Speaker Ramesh Tawadkar dismissed the disqualification petition against eight MLAs who switched from Congress to BJP. He cited a Supreme Court ruling that protected their actions as two-thirds of the Congress legislature party members approved the merger, preventing disqualification under the 10th schedule.
title: Plea to disqualify 8 Congress MLAs who joined BJP in Goa junked

description: The Madras High Court has directed the Tamil Nadu government to establish Child Tobacco Cessation Centres in all districts to counsel and treat students addicted to 'Cool Lip,' a banned tobacco product. The court mandated periodic inspections in schools and urged the Centre to officially ban 'Cool Lip.'
title: Set up child tobacco help centres: High Court

description: Canadian police arrested Abhijeet Kingra, linked to the Lawrence Bishnoi gang, after a shooting at singer AP Dhillon's home in Victoria Island. An arrest warrant is out for second suspect Vikram Sharma, believed to be in India. The attack followed Dhillon's latest music release featuring Salman Khan. Kingra faces multiple charges including discharging a firearm.
title: Bishnoi 'foot soldier' held in Canada for shooting and arson

description: Apple's revenue in India hit an all-time record due to increased sales of iPhones and other products like iPads, MacBooks, and AirPods. CEO Tim Cook highlighted India's growing importance, noting the expansion in production and retail presence. The company's global net sales rose over 6% to $95 billion for the quarter.
title: Apple's India revenue hits a new high in September quarter

description: A roadside bomb explosion near a girls' school in Mastung district, Balochistan, killed seven people, including five children and a police constable, and injured over 20 others. The attack involved an IED fitted inside a motorcycle and targeted a police mobile and a school van passing by.
title: Roadside blast kills 7, five of them schoolchildren, in Pakistan

description: Elon Musk is from South Africa and he dismissed allegations that he violated US immigration law. Even President Joe Biden spoke about the issue as he said, "That wealthiest man in the world turned out to be an illegal worker here when he was here." “He was supposed to be in school when he came on a student visa. He wasn’t in school. He was violating the law. He’s talking about all these ‘illegals’ coming our way,” Biden said.
title: Elon Musk reacts to reports that he could be deported for immigration violation

description: A bomb threat caused panic on the Bihar Sampark Kranti Express travelling to New Delhi. According to the officials, the Gonda unit received information from the Delhi control room over a bomb threat. The train was halted and searched at Gonda junction, but no explosives were found.  Authorities are investigating to identify the sender of the hoax threat.
title: Bihar Sampark Kranti Express train receives bomb threat

description: Delhi's air quality plummets to 'very poor' levels post-Diwali due to increased firecracker usage, stubble burning, and local emissions. Favorable weather conditions, including high wind speeds and above-normal temperatures, prevent it from reaching 'severe' levels. Authorities warn of worsening pollution in the coming days due to rising stubble burning incidents.
title: Weather rescues city’s air: 2nd cleanest post-Diwali since 2015

description: Donald Trump criticized Liz Cheney as a 'dumb and radical war hawk,' suggesting she should be subjected to gunfire. This remark underscores his violent rhetoric and sexism, further alienating college-educated women voters. Trump's comments also reignited debate about his disrespect for women's rights and his previous misconduct allegations.
title: Women fire back at Trump after he shoots his mouth saying 'war hawk' Liz Cheney should be fired on

description: Two migrant workers from UP were injured in a suspected terrorist attack in Budgam, Kashmir, making it the sixth such incident in J&K this year. Security forces cordoned off the area. The attack follows recent similar incidents, including the killing of a migrant labourer and a barber from UP being shot earlier this month.
title: J&K: 2 migrant workers from UP injured in year's 6th targeted terror attack

description: China expressed strong objection to repeated terror attacks on its citizens in Pakistan, warning it might reconsider investments under the Belt and Road Initiative. The Chinese ambassador contradicted Pakistan's deputy PM, and urged Islamabad to implement effective security measures following recent deadly attacks.
title: Beijing breakpoint over 'unacceptable' terror attacks, Pakistan 'perplexed'

description: Democrat Suhas Subramanyam, a Virginia state senator and Indian American candidate, is running for the US House of Representatives. He emphasizes comprehensive immigration reform, fair green card quotas, healthcare access, and economic ties between the US and India, while highlighting Indian American representation in politics.
title: Democrat Suhas Subramanyam supports easier path to green card for H-1B holders

description: Thai YouTuber Natthamon Khongchak, known as 'Nutty,' was arrested after evading authorities for two years. She defrauded thousands of followers with a fake forex investment scheme. Promising high returns, she fled to Indonesia with her mother when the promised earnings did not materialize. They were caught and extradited back to Thailand.
title: Thai YouTuber 'Nutty' caught after failing Indonesia's national anthem test

description: Kolkata junior medics are unhappy with the slow pace of the RG Kar rape and murder case investigation, questioning the thoroughness of the probe into suspects, including former hospital principal Sandip Ghosh. They plan statewide rallies to demand clarity and accountability from authorities.
title: RG Kar case: Kolkata docs question CBI, announce slew of protests

description: In a crucial NFL game against the Houston Texans, Aaron Rodgers' decisive deep pass to Garrett Wilson set up a remarkable one-handed catch, securing a victory for the New York Jets. This memorable play not only highlights Wilson’s exceptional skills but also raises questions about his future with Adidas.
title: Jets Star’s 'Michael Jordan Moment' puts $42 Billion Giant deal at risk

description: Celebrated designer Rohit Bal, known as 'Gudda,' has passed away, leaving a significant legacy in Indian fashion. The FDCI mourns his loss, praising his contributions to couture through his innovative blending of traditional and contemporary designs. Bal's signature motifs and commitment to craftsmanship have influenced generations of designers globally.
title: Fashion designer Rohit Bal passes away

description: In reaction to PM Modi's comments, Congress President Mallikarjun Kharge criticized the BJP's 100-day plan, calling it mere publicity. Kharge questioned the government's claims, labeling them deceitful. He raised questions like unemployment, rising prices, and economic inequality, accusing the BJP of broken promises and financial mismanagement. He also challenged the authenticity of BJP’s policies and initiatives.
title: 'Lies, deceit & fakery': Kharge fires salvo at PM Modi, Centre

description: Deepika Padukone and Ranveer Singh welcomed their baby girl on September 8 this year, and fans were eager to get a glimpse of the little one for a long time. Finally, Deepika and Ranveer shared an adorable picture of their daughter, in which she is seen wearing an elegant red Diwali outfit.
title: Deepika Padukone and Ranveer Singh name their daughter 'Dua Padukone Singh'
3 bears on prowl in J&K's Doda, man injured; authorities launch search operation
Terror attack in J&K: Two non-local people shot at by terrorists in Budgam district

description: Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah criticizes PM Modi for accusing his government of making 'fake' promises, asserting they are fulfilling their commitments with a significant budget. He also condemns BJP’s past corruption and accuses the central government of exploiting Karnataka by withholding deserved funds.
title: 'No one lies like PM Modi': Cong hits out at BJP's 'disastrous legacy'

description: In the 2024 US presidential election, Indian-Americans, with approximately 2.6 million eligible voters, are becoming crucial in key battleground states. Their historical Democratic lean is shifting, with notable rises in Republican interest, especially among younger male voters, impacting candidates' strategies. The decline in Democratic identification and the rising interest in Republican candidates, especially among younger men, suggest a potential realignment that both parties must heed.
title: Harris or Trump? 10 charts explain who Indian-Americans may vote for on Nov 5

description: The government's effort to privatise Pakistan International Airlines (PIA) failed as the only bidder, Blue World City, offered PKR 10 billion for a 60% stake, significantly lower than the PKR 85.03 billion minimum. The lack of competition and high government demands discouraged other bidders.
title: Pakistan gets measly $36m offer for debt-ridden flag carrier

description: Indonesia has banned the sale of Google Pixel smartphones due to non-compliance with local manufacturing regulations, aiming to boost domestic production. This follows a similar ban on Apple's iPhone 16. Both companies failed to meet the requirement of at least 40% locally-sourced components, impacting their ability to sell and operate in the country.
title: After Apple iPhone, Indonesia bans this Google phone

description: Eastern Spain faces its deadliest flooding in Valencia, resulting in over 205 deaths. Torrential rains caused flash floods, worsened by climate change and poor urban planning. Late warnings and lack of risk awareness further contribute to the disaster, highlighting the need for improved emergency education.
title: Spain reels from deadliest floods in decades: Why did over 205 lives end in tragedy?

description: After being accused of calling Shiv Sena candidate Shaina NC 'imported maal,' UBT MP Arvind Sawant insists he did not name her and claims defamation. He emphasizes his respect for Shaina and accuses PM Modi of dishonesty. A case is filed against Sawant, with Shaina calling for an apology. The Maharashtra Assembly election is on November 20.
title: 'Shaina NC my friend': Sawant defends 'imported maal' remark, says he's a victim

description: In the 2024 US presidential election, Indian-Americans, with approximately 2.6 million eligible voters, are becoming crucial in key battleground states. Their historical Democratic lean is shifting, with notable rises in Republican interest, especially among younger male voters, impacting candidates' strategies. The decline in Democratic identification and the rising interest in Republican candidates, especially among younger men, suggest a potential realignment that both parties must heed.
title: Harris or Trump? 10 charts explain who Indian-Americans may vote for on Nov 5

description: Bigg Boss 18 introduces wild card contestants Kashish Kapoor and Digvijay Rathee, their reunion sparking intense drama recalling their past rivalry from Splitsvilla X5. Host Salman Khan mediates their heated exchange as the contestants join the show, adding more excitement and twists to the ongoing season.
title: Bigg Boss 18: Salman Khan looks annoyed, 'hogaya aapka'

description: Govardhan Puja is a time for devotion and community, showcasing the importance of faith and gratitude in Hindu culture. To make this beautiful occasion more special, we present to you a specially curated list of heartwarming Images, Quotes, Wishes, Messages, Cards, Greetings, Pictures, and GIFs to share with your loved ones on this day!
title: Happy Govardhan Puja 2024: Images, Quotes, Wishes and GIFs

description: India initially dominated on the first day against New Zealand with a strong 53-run partnership but then suffered a collapse, losing three wickets in just 8 balls. Late dismissals of Yashasvi Jaiswal, Mohammed Siraj, and Virat Kohli left them at 86 for 4 at stumps, trailing New Zealand by another 149 runs at close of play.
title: 15 minutes, 8 balls, 3 wickets! India lose plot late on Day 1

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi criticized the Congress for making unrealistic promises while failing to deliver on them in states like Karnataka, Himachal Pradesh, and Telangana. He emphasized that such false assurances harm the poor, youngsters, farmers, and women, and result in fiscal instability and diluted existing schemes.
title: 'Congress stands badly exposed': PM Modi's scathing attack over 'unfulfilled guarantees'

description: Apple CEO Tim Cook wished everyone a joyous Diwali on social media, sharing a stunning photograph of traditional oil lamps by Delhi-born photographer Rohit Vohra, taken with an iPhone 16 Pro Max. Vohra expressed his delight at having his work highlighted and praised the advanced camera features of the device.
title: Apple CEO Tim Cook shares Diwali wishes with these iPhone photos

description: GST collections in October grossed Rs 1.87 lakh crore, reflecting an 8.9% year-on-year increase. From January to October 2024, collections rose to Rs 12.74 lakh crore. April 2024 saw record collections of Rs 2.1 lakh crore. The overall fiscal year 2023-24 collections experienced an 11.7% rise, suggesting strong domestic consumption and import activity.
title: GST collections surge 9% in October, reaching Rs 1.87 lakh crore

description: Indian spinner Ravindra Jadeja expressed surprise at the team's late collapse against New Zealand, falling from a promising start to 86/4 by the end of Day 1. Jadeja's five-wicket haul and Washington Sundar's four helped bowl New Zealand out for 235, emphasizing the need for small partnerships to surpass this target.
title: Jadeja says India's late collapse 'unexpected'

description: The Burj Khalifa in Dubai recently lit up to celebrate Diwali, showcasing intricate patterns and a festive message, which became a viral hit with over 345,000 views. Social media users praised Dubai's cultural inclusiveness. The Emaar Group, who constructed the Burj Khalifa, highlighted the event on social media, reflecting Dubai's commitment to honoring global celebrations.
title: Burj Khalifa shines for Diwali: Watch UAE's tallest tribute to festival of lights

description: Delhi chief minister Atishi declared a public holiday on November 7 for Chhath Puja, following a request from lieutenant governor V K Saxena. This Hindu festival, mainly celebrated in Bihar and eastern Uttar Pradesh, involves a four-day routine of worshipping the sun god. Announcement aims to enable the Purvanchal community to celebrate fully.
title: Delhi govt declares public holiday on November 7 for Chhath Puja

description: India's batting faltered at Wankhede on the opening day of the third Test against New Zealand, ending at 86/4 in response to New Zealand's 235. Earlier, Ravindra Jadeja's five-wicket haul and Washington Sundar's four-wicket performance highlighted India's bowling. However, a late collapse left India trailing by 149 runs, with key wickets falling in quick succession.
title: 3rd Test: India commit harakiri late on Day 1 to hand NZ control

description: A case is filed against Shiv Sena (UBT) MP Arvind Sawant for derogatory remarks about Shiv Sena's Shaina NC. Sawant referred to women as 'maal' during a campaign event, prompting Shaina to condemn the disrespectful language and warning of electoral repercussions for referring to professional women inappropriately.
title: Shaina NC files defamation case over Sawant's 'imported maal' remark

description: Diwali Muhurat Trading 2024 stocks to buy: NSE and BSE will hold their annual Muhurat Trading session on Friday, a favorable time for investments.  Here is a list of small cap, mid-cap and large-cap stocks for Samvat 2081 with a view till next Diwali:
title: Diwali Muhurat trading: Top stocks to buy in Samvat 2081 - check list

description: On the first day of the final Test between India and New Zealand, Indian bowlers struggled with multiple no-ball infractions despite early breakthroughs. Commentator Ravi Shastri humorously noted Sunil Gavaskar's likely frustration with these errors. Off-spinner Washington Sundar led in no-balls, causing five infractions by the middle of the second session.
title: 'Washington would've been close to Washington DC', quips Shastri

description: Devender Singh Rana, BJP MLA from Nagrota in Jammu and Kashmir, passed away at 59. His remains were brought to Jammu on Friday. His death has drawn condolences from political leaders including Prime Minister Narendra Modi and Union Home Minister Amit Shah, who acknowledged his contributions to the region's progress and peace.
title: J&K BJP MLA Devender Singh Rana's mortal remains brought to his home in Jammu

description: The Alphabet Workers Union has filed a complaint with the NLRB, accusing Google of illegally restricting employees from discussing its search antitrust case.
title: Google told employees not to talk about ...: Workers Union to court

description: Ravindra Jadeja's outstanding bowling dismantled New Zealand's innings in the third Test against India, as he took five wickets. New Zealand, having started well, were bowled out for 235 despite a solid partnership between Will Young and Daryl Mitchell. Jadeja's 14th five-wicket haul and Washington Sundar's four wickets capped off an impressive performance.
title: Double-wicket over, twice! Ravindra Jadeja rocks New Zealand

description: He added: “We will also protect Hindu Americans against the anti-religion agenda of the radical left. We will fight for your freedom. Under my administration, we will also strengthen our great partnership with India and my good friend, Prime Minister Modi. Kamala Harris will destroy your small businesses with more regulations and higher taxes. By contrast, I cut taxes, cut regulations, unleashed American energy, and built the greatest economy in history. We will do it again, bigger and better than ever before—and we will Make America Great Again. Also, Happy Diwali to All. I hope the Festival of Lights leads to the Victory of Good over Evil!”
title: Trump praised on social media for speaking up for Hindus in Bangladesh

description: At the 1936 Berlin Olympics, Indian marathon runner CSA Swami, aged 22, kept German dictator Adolf Hitler waiting as he vowed to complete the marathon despite being far behind. Swami's insistence on finishing the race epitomised true sportsmanship and caused a delay in the closing ceremony.
title: The Indian marathoner who kept Hitler waiting at 1936 Berlin Olympics
‘Brat’ named Collins word of the year, embraced by Charli XCX fans and Kamala Harris supporters

description: BJP MP Ravi Shankar Prasad criticizes Congress for its 'Shakti scheme,' accusing it of making misleading and empty promises. He demands an apology from Congress leaders Mallikarjun Kharge and Rahul Gandhi. Prasad highlights issues in Himachal Pradesh and Karnataka as examples of Congress's unfulfilled pledges, while Kharge advises caution in announcing fiscally responsible schemes.
title: 'Congress accepted they misled public': BJP demands apology from Kharge, Rahul Gandhi

description: Rahul Gandhi and his nephew Raihan Vadra celebrated Diwali by learning pottery and painting from local artisans in New Delhi to understand the challenges faced by these workers. Rahul emphasized the importance of acknowledging and supporting the skilled laborers who bring light to homes amidst their own struggles.
title: Watch: Rahul Gandhi spends Diwali with those 'who brighten India'

description: The Congress criticized the Election Commission for its generic and condescending response to complaints about irregularities in Haryana elections. The EC's dismissal of allegations as baseless and its defence of EVM battery statuses were highlighted, alongside Congress’s claims of biased treatment compared to actions against BJP leaders. "If the EC's goal is to strip itself of last vestiges of neutrality, then it's doing remarkable job at creating that impression," the Congress said.
title: 'Reply laced with attacks': Cong slams EC's 'condescending tone', warns of legal action

description: Rishabh Pant has been surprisingly released by Delhi Capitals after an eight-year stint, prompting speculation of his move to Chennai Super Kings for IPL 2025. With MS Dhoni expected to play his last IPL season next year, Pant's transition to CSK seems likely as they look for a quality wicketkeeper-batsman.
title: 'Something big to happen!' Raina drops mega hint about Pant

description: Kunal Kamra has intensified his criticism against Ola Electric's after-sales service, taking potshots at CEO Bhavish Aggarwal through social media. Kamra mocked Aggarwal's Diwali celebration video, demanding footage of service centres. Their ongoing feud began over customer complaints and poor service, with Kamra sarcastically accepting Aggarwal's challenge to work at a service centre.
title: Kunal Kamra vs Ola: The fight continues with ‘service centre dikhao’ jab

description: Google CEO Sundar Pichai wished everyone a bright and joyful Diwali on social media, highlighting the festival's essence of warmth and light. He shared a festive image featuring a traditional lantern adorned with the Google logo amidst vibrant Diwali decorations. Google India also extended Diwali greetings across various social platforms, adding to the festive spirit.
title: CEO Sundar Pichai shares Diwali greeting with picture of ‘Google rocket’

description: Virat Kohli entertained fans by dancing to the Bollywood song 'My Name is Lakhan' during the first day of the third Test between India and New Zealand at the Wankhede Stadium in Mumbai. His playful dance moves quickly went viral. Kohli was also retained by Royal Challengers Bengaluru (RCB) for the next three IPL seasons with a contract worth Rs 21 crore.
title: Kohli entertains fans with epic dance moves. WATCH

description: Indian Army resumes patrolling in Eastern Ladakh's Demchok sector and plans patrols in Depsang after Chinese obstruction since 2020, following a recent agreement between India and China. The two armies completed disengagement, while maintaining significant troop deployments along the LAC in Ladakh and across Arunachal Pradesh and Sikkim.
title: 'Indian troops' patrolling in Demchok sector begins after LAC pact with China'

description: Kansas City Chiefs tight end Travis Kelce is expanding his talents beyond football with acting roles in shows like FX’s “Grotesquerie” and a cameo in “Happy Gilmore 2.” He also participates in a Christmas album alongside his brother Jason, featuring R&B group Boyz II Men, aiming to raise funds for local charities.
title: Travis & Jason Kelce join hands with Boyz II Men for the new holiday single

description: An explosion in Balochistan's Mastung during a polio vaccination drive killed seven people, including five schoolchildren and a policeman. The blast, involving an IED attached to a motorcycle, injured 22 others. Authorities suspect separatist groups behind the attack; no group has claimed responsibility yet.
title: Blast in Pakistan’s Balochistan kills 7, including 5 children, during polio vaccination drive

description: Senator JD Vance claims that social pressures may influence affluent parents to encourage their teens to identify as transgender for better chances at Ivy League admissions. He and Joe Rogan express concerns over pharmaceutical gender transitions and the impact of biological males competing in female sports.
title: JD Vance suggests teens ‘becoming trans’ for college benefits

description: Toxic foam floating on the Yamuna River in Delhi's Kalindi Kunj area ahead of Chhath Puja has raised pollution concerns. BJP leader Shehzad Poonawalla blamed Delhi Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal for the pollution, while local authorities have started spraying chemical defoamers. Additionally, thick smog after Diwali has pushed the city's air quality into the 'very poor' category.
title: Toxic foam in Yamuna raises pollution concerns in Delhi ahead of Chhath Puja

description: Sarfaraz Khan's continuous chirping during the first day of the third Test at the Wankhede Stadium in Mumbai irritated New Zealand's Daryl Mitchell, leading to a pitch-side discussion involving umpires and Indian skipper Rohit Sharma. Despite this, New Zealand, after early setbacks, managed to recover, with Young and Mitchell stabilizing their innings.
title: 'Chatty' Sarfaraz irritates Mitchell, Rohit stands up for his mate

description: Muhurat Trading 2024: Stock exchanges in India will be closed for regular trading on November 1, 2024, following Diwali celebrations, with a special Muhurat trading session in the evening. Indian markets have in the past year experienced significant gains with Nifty rising 25% and broader indices showing even more substantial growth.
title: Diwali Muhurat trading 2024: Check timings for special stock market session

description: In Delhi's Shahdara, a 40-year-old man and his 16-year-old nephew were fatally shot while celebrating Diwali. Two armed men attacked them, also injuring his 10-year-old son. Police suspect personal enmity as the motive. Akash Sharma and Rishabh Sharma succumbed to their injuries, while Krish Sharma remains hospitalized. Authorities are investigating further.
title: On cam: Man, his nephew killed, 1 injured in firing in Delhi's Shahdara

description: A five-year-old boy was injured after a motorist smashed his car window with a stone in southeast Bengaluru. The father claims the attack was unprovoked, but the motorist alleges it followed a hit-and-run by the father. Police have arrested a man for aiding the attacker.
title: Watch: Road rage in Bengaluru? Man attacks family in car, hurts kid

description: Renowned economist Bibek Debroy, former Chairman of the Economic Advisory Council to India's Prime Minister, passed away at 69. He led key policy initiatives and had an impressive academic and professional career. His notable work includes translations of the Mahabharata.
title: Who was Bibek Debroy? Renowned economist leaves behind a legacy

description: The African CDC has warned that the mpox outbreak remains uncontrolled, with most deaths in the Democratic Republic of Congo. A highly contagious clade 1b variant has now been detected in the UK. Mpox spreads primarily through close contact with infected individuals, and its symptoms include fever, rash, and swollen lymph nodes.
title: Mpox not under control as deadly variant found in the UK

description: Russia has fined Google $20 decillion for not reinstating banned pro-Kremlin YouTube channels. The unprecedented sum corresponds to penalties starting in 2020, growing exponentially under Russian law. Legal claims against Google span multiple countries. Google's parent company views the disputes as unlikely to have substantial adverse effects.
title: Why Russia has fined Google more than the GDP of the entire world

description: Apple CEO Tim Cook announced plans for four new retail stores in Bengaluru, Pune, Mumbai, and Delhi-NCR. These expansions are expected to employ around 400 people, bolstering the company’s growing success in India. Apple recorded an all-time revenue high in India for Q4 2024, driven by strong iPhone sales and increased manufacturing.
title: CEO Tim Cook confirms this 'big news' about Apple India plans

description: On the IPL 2025 retention deadline, several prominent players, including Rishabh Pant, KL Rahul and Jos Buttler, were released by their teams. While Pant's departure from Delhi Capitals is the most surprising, other notable omissions include Arshdeep Singh, Ishan Kishan and Shreyas Iyer. These players now move to the auction pool.
title: IPL Retentions: Top 10 players who haven't been retained

description: BJP leader Shehzad Poonawalla accuses Jharkhand CM Hemant Soren and his party, JMM, of corruption and inconsistencies in affidavits, questioning Soren's fluctuating declared age. JMM dismisses claims as politically motivated. The Jharkhand Assembly elections are scheduled for November, involving 2.60 crore voters.
title: 'JMM means Jhol, Muslim appeasement and Mafia': BJP accuses Soren of age fraud

description: North Korea tested the Hwasong-19 ICBM, claiming it as the world's strongest with enhanced altitude and flight capabilities. Kim Jong Un described it as a response to national security threats. Officials suggest solid fuel technology was used, offering faster launches. Meanwhile, international criticism arises over North Korea's troop deployment to Russia.
title: North Korea says test-fire perfected new missile 'Hwasong-19': What it means

description: At least 12 devotees sustained minor injuries after slipping on hills at Deviramma temple in Chikkamagaluru during heavy rain on Thursday. The annual festival drew hundreds of visitors despite the challenging weather. Authorities had taken safety measures, and all injured were safely rescued. The festival will conclude on November 3.
title: Karnataka: Several devotees injured as thousands throng to Deviramma temple

description: Bibek Debroy, a renowned economist and chairman of the Prime Minister’s economic advisory council, passed away at 69. He was celebrated for his contributions to economic theory, policy, and social equity advocacy. Debroy also led the Finance Ministry's committee on infrastructure and framed strategic growth policies for India.
title: Chairman of PM’s economic advisory council Bibek Debroy passes away

description: Police arrested Abjeet Kingra for discharging a firearm and arson in a shooting outside Punjabi singer AP Dhillon's home linked to the Lawrence Bishnoi gang. They are still searching for Vikram Sharma in India. The incident may be linked to Dhillon’s association with Salman Khan and portrayal of gangster culture.
title: Shooting near AP Dhillon's home in Canada: One arrested, another missing

description: Israeli forces intercepted UAVs allegedly targeting the south, attributed to the Iran-supported Islamic Resistance of Iraq. This follows rocket attacks from Lebanon causing casualties in northern Israel. Israel retaliated with strikes in Beirut and broader Lebanon amid escalating conflicts with Hezbollah, Hamas, and Iran-backed groups.
title: Watch: Israeli air defenses fire interceptor missiles to target drones

description: Rohit Sharma has been retained by Mumbai Indians along with Hardik Pandya, Suryakumar Yadav, Jasprit Bumrah, and Tilak Varma ahead of the upcoming IPL auction. Following a disappointing 2024 season, Rohit is optimistic about the franchise building a strong team for the 2025 edition. Having retired from international T20s, he feels staying with Mumbai Indians is ideal for him.
title: Retained Rohit vows to 'bring the MI legacy back where it belongs'

description: A journalist was killed and his colleague injured in a knife attack in Uttar Pradesh's Fatehpur district. The incident took place near the Bhitaura bypass, reportedly due to a land dispute. Police have arrested four suspects and filed a case against seven named and several unknown individuals. The investigation is ongoing.
title: Journalist killed, colleague injured in knife attack in UP, 4 arrested

description: Apple's fiscal Q4 2024 results exceeded expectations with $94.93 billion revenue, a 6% rise year-over-year, setting a September quarter record. Key figures include $46.22 billion from iPhone sales. Despite a $10 billion hit from a tax charge, Apple sustained strong performances across all product categories and regions.
title: Apple iPhone 16 is a 'hit', and this may be the proof

description: India aims to advance beyond the current disengagement with China along the LAC, requiring patience, as stated by Defence Minister Rajnath Singh. Talks between both nations have led to a broad consensus. Singh emphasized national unity and the Northeast's role in India's development.
title: Disengagement with China almost complete: Rajnath

description: A 24-year-old man named Siddu confronted his girlfriend in Padmanabhanagar about her new relationship with Mohan. During the confrontation, Mohan aggressively assaulted Siddu. Despite Siddu’s brother intervening, both siblings were attacked. The police have registered the case under sections related to causing hurt and provoking a breach of peace.
title: Bengaluru youth catches girlfriend with another lover, punched in face

description: Former President Trump vowed to protect Hindu Americans from the radical left's anti-religion agenda, pledged to strengthen US-India relations, and condemned violence against minorities in Bangladesh. Trump contrasted his administration's policies with those of Biden and Harris, emphasizing economic growth and regulatory reform.
title: ‘Will strengthen partnership with PM Modi’: Trump's Diwali message to Hindu Americans

description: In Mumbai, outgoing state cabinet ministers saw increased net assets over five years, notably CM Eknath Shinde with a 187% rise. Aditi Tatkare had a 772% increase. Three ministers face money laundering investigations. RTI activist Shailesh Gandhi urges scrutiny of election affidavits, emphasizing income source verification. Mangal Prabhat Lodha's assets decreased by 11%.
title: Assets of ministers Aditi Tatkare, Sanjay Rathod and CM soar in 5 years

description: History sheets at Kolkata police stations will now exclude names of minors and innocent individuals who were previously listed due to socio-economic status. This change follows Supreme Court guidelines recommending amendments to the 1943 Police Regulations of Bengal. The sheets, meant for internal police use, will now only include those aiding criminals on the run.
title: In Bengal, names of innocents, minors to go off history sheets

description: Nicholas Pooran, retained as Lucknow Super Giants' top player, expresses gratitude to the franchise for their trust. He is available for captaincy, focusing on scoring runs and fostering a winning atmosphere. Pooran reflects on relinquishing West Indies captaincy, its impact on his growth, and aims for team success.
title: At LSG, I want to create a winning atmosphere: Nicholas Pooran

description: New Zealand are on the brink of an unprecedented 3-0 whitewash against India after securing their maiden series win in the country. The third Test at Wankhede Stadium is crucial for India, not just for pride but also for World Test Championship contention. India's senior players face significant scrutiny amid their struggles this series.
title: IND vs NZ: Pride on line for battered Team India at the Wankhede

description: Three Indian cricket stars, Rishabh Pant, Shreyas Iyer, and KL Rahul, are up for grabs in the IPL auction. Teams like Mumbai Indians and Sunrisers Hyderabad made key retentions, including MI keeping core players like Hardik Pandya as captain. LSG’s owner hinted at leadership preference changes. The auction promises significant reshuffling among franchises.
title: IPL's big Diwali release: Shreyas Iyer, KL Rahul & Rishabh Pant

description: In his annual letter, Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella reflects on the company's focus on AI and its impact on various sectors. He highlights Microsoft's achievements in AI progress, financial performance, and future priorities including security, trustworthy AI innovation, and cost management. Nadella emphasizes the company's mission to empower people globally through technology and continuous innovation.
title: Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella addresses shareholders in his annual letter

description: JPMorgan Chase CEO Jamie Dimon vehemently opposes several major US financial regulatory initiatives, arguing they could hinder innovation, increase consumer costs, and weaken the financial system. He specifically criticizes the Basel III endgame proposal, the Federal Reserve's capital surcharge, and the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau's open banking rule.
title: CEO of US' largest bank JPMorgan CEO says 'Time to fight back as things are ...'

description: By 2070, climate change could result in a 24.7% GDP loss for India and a 16.9% GDP loss for the Asia-Pacific region due to rising sea levels and reduced productivity. Lower-income economies will be most affected. Immediate and coordinated climate action is essential to mitigate these economic impacts and address rising emissions, particularly from China.
title: India may face 25% GDP loss by '70 due to climate change: Study

description: CM Siddaramaiah clarified there is no proposal to review any government guarantee schemes, including the Shakthi scheme offering free bus travel for women, despite D K Shivakumar's remarks. Siddaramaiah mentioned he would discuss the matter with Shivakumar, who noted some women prefer paying for their tickets.
title: No plans to review free bus ride, other guarantees: Sidda

description: Tension erupted in Kadakol village, Haveri district, after villagers, fearing Waqf Board's takeover of their properties, attacked a specific community's buildings, injuring five. Police restored peace, detained 32 for investigation. Waqf minister B Z Zameer Ahmed Khan blamed BJP for misleading farmers. Verification of Waqf property claims is underway.
title: Fear of Waqf taking over houses sets off violence in Karnataka village

description: The BJP has announced statewide protests from November 4, demanding minister BZ Zameer Ahmed Khan's resignation over claims of farmland being transferred to the waqf board. State BJP president BY Vijayendra and former CM Basavaraj Bommai accused the Congress government of altering land records. CM Siddaramaiah countered, asserting BJP's political motives and promising to rescind any contentious notices.
title: Waqf land row: Karnataka BJP to launch statewide stir on Nov 4
